subSubSection.paragraph:
Redescription.
WORKER (n=6) (
Fig. 41A–C
): HL 0.92 (0.85–0.94); HW 0.80 (0.77–0.82); ML 0.58 (0.54–0.60); SL 0.81 (0.74–0.85); MOD 0.25 (0.22–0.28); PNW 0.58 (0.54–0.60); WL 1.20 (1.10–1.22); PSL 0.28 (0.25–0.32); PL 0.54 (0.50–0.58); PW 0.18 (0.18–0.20); PPL 0.29 (0.28–0.32); PPW 0.29 (0.26–0.30); GL 1.12 (1.04–1.12); TL 4.65 (4.33–4.78); CI 86.95 (86.95–90.58); SI 101.25 (95–103.66); OI 31.25 (28.20–34.14). Small to midsized. Shiny integument. Bicolored body, brownish with lighter leg. Many branched setae, midsized to short, branches of equal size (
Fig. 80I
), suberect to subdecumbent; unbranched setae predominate in the gaster.
